                                Read More &gt;</a>
                        </div>

                        <div class='white-card recent-post clearfix extra-padding'>
                            <h5 class='recent-post-header'>
                                PHP-DI 3.3 released
                            </h5>

                            <p class='post-content'>
                                I am happy to announce that PHP-DI version 3.3 has just been released.
                                The major new feature is the possibility to inject all dependencies of an existing instance.
                            </p>
                            <a href="{{ baseUrl }}/news/03-php-di-3-3.html" class="btn btn-extra pull-right">
                                Read More &gt;</a>
                        </div>

                        <div class='white-card recent-post clearfix extra-padding'>
                            <h5 class='recent-post-header'>
                                PHP-DI 3.2 released
                            </h5>

                            <p class='post-content'>
                                I am happy to announce that I have just released PHP-DI version 3.2.
                                The major new feature is the full support of Lazy Injection.
                                But first, let's talk about the `ContainerBuilder`.
                            </p>
                            <a href="{{ baseUrl }}/news/02-php-di-3-2.html" class="btn btn-extra pull-right">
                                Read More &gt;</a>
                        </div>

                        <div class='white-card recent-post clearfix extra-padding'>
                            <h5 class='recent-post-header'>
                                PHP-DI 3.1 released
                            </h5>

                            <p class='post-content'>
                                I am happy to announce that I have just released PHP-DI version 3.1.
                                The major new feature is the Zend Framework 1 integration.
                                You can now use PHP-DI very easily with ZF1, and the integration will provide
                                you dependency injection into your controllers.
                            </p>
                            <a href="{{ baseUrl }}/news/01-php-di-3-1.html" class="btn btn-extra pull-right">
                                Read More &gt;</a>
                        </div>

